      <section class="dbc-section dbc-top-section dbc-element dbc-element-6853031 dbc-section-boxed dbc-section-height-default dbc-section-height-default" data-id="6853031" data-element_type="section">
        <div class="dbc-container dbc-column-gap-default">
          <div class="dbc-column dbc-col-100 dbc-top-column dbc-element dbc-element-c22756b" data-id="c22756b" data-element_type="column">
            <div class="dbc-widget-wrap dbc-element-populated">
              <div class="dbc-element dbc-element-44c55e5 dbc-widget dbc-widget-text-editor" data-id="44c55e5" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
                <div class="dbc-widget-container">
                  <ul><li><p class="gs_rt"><a id="bxExQBZdyEQJ" href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0014482709003449" data-clk="hl=en&amp;sa=T&amp;ct=res&amp;cd=0&amp;d=4956313740068852079&amp;ei=1UWKZOPBNMuKywSUn5iABQ" data-clk-atid="bxExQBZdyEQJ"><b>Mesenchymal stem cells </b>induce <b>dermal </b>fibroblast responses to injury</a></p></li><li><p class="gs_rt"><a id="xc7-QqvNegsJ" href="https://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/ben/cscr/2017/00000012/00000001/art00010" data-clk="hl=en&amp;sa=T&amp;ct=res&amp;cd=2&amp;d=827199617023004357&amp;ei=1UWKZOPBNMuKywSUn5iABQ" data-clk-atid="xc7-QqvNegsJ">Role of <b>mesenchymal stem cells </b>in <b>dermal </b>repair in burns and diabetic wounds</a></p></li><li><p class="gs_rt"><a id="-Y-fQc4as1oJ" href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0190962209012195" data-clk="hl=en&amp;sa=T&amp;ct=res&amp;cd=5&amp;d=6535596957411282937&amp;ei=1UWKZOPBNMuKywSUn5iABQ" data-clk-atid="-Y-fQc4as1oJ">Skin <b>mesenchymal stem cells</b>: prospects for clinical dermatology</a></p></li><li><p class="gs_rt"><a id="WgV1oOeL-5gJ" href="https://anatomypubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/1097-0177(2000)9999:9999%3C::AID-DVDY1037%3E3.0.CO;2-7" data-clk="hl=en&amp;sa=T&amp;ct=res&amp;cd=7&amp;d=11023558339865150810&amp;ei=1UWKZOPBNMuKywSUn5iABQ" data-clk-atid="WgV1oOeL-5gJ">Dilution of human <b>mesenchymal stem cells </b>with <b>dermal </b>fibroblasts and the effects on in vitro and in vivo osteochondrogenesis</a></p></li><li><p class="gs_rt"><a id="S70nnBQfV-kJ" href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/lary.20860" data-clk="hl=en&amp;sa=T&amp;ct=res&amp;cd=0&amp;d=16813941907190693195&amp;ei=V0aKZOH3OqKbywSeir5w" data-clk-atid="S70nnBQfV-kJ">Effect of neural‐induced <b>mesenchymal stem cells </b>and platelet‐rich plasma on <b>facial </b>nerve regeneration in an acute nerve injury model</a></p></li></ul><h2><span style="color: #000000;">Step by Step stem cell facial restoration</span></h2><ol><li><span style="color: #000000;">A numbing cream is applied to the face to prevent pain</span></li><li><span style="color: #000000;">The doctor mixes the 20 million mesenchymal stem cells and PRP into a syringe</span></li><li><span style="color: #000000;">The face is then injected with a small insulin type syringe into the areas that have the most wrinkles. Then the rest of the face is injected.</span></li><li><span style="color: #000000;"> PRP is loaded into the TKN mesoject gun then applied across the whole face. </span></li></ol><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>There is no scarring from this procedure and any redness on the face is gone by the next day. We do advise that you avoid the sun for the next few days.</strong></span></p><p><span style="color: #000000;">We do not apply to the neck as this area does not have the same collagen and fat below the skin as the face. The <a href="https://dreambody.clinic/index.php/stem-cells-to-reverse-aging-anti-aging-stem-cell-treatment/">stem cell IV treatments</a> are best for skin rejuvenation.</span></p><h2><span style="color: #000000;">Side Effects or Risks</span></h2><p><span style="color: #000000;">The only side effects that have been documented are the following:</span></p><ul><li><span style="color: #000000;">The Patients face will be red for 2 to 3 days post treatment</span></li><li><span style="color: #000000;">As with any treatment involving injections there is a small chance of infection. We use sterile techniques to prevent infection and have never had an infection.</span></li><li><span style="color: #000000;">We do not treat patients that have had cancer within the past 5 years. There is still no conclusive evidence linking stem cells to make cancer worse, but we prefer to stay on the side of safety until more research has been done on cancer effects from stem cells. So far research points towards stem cells having a positive effect on many cancers, but we are not focused on cancer treatments.</span></li><li><span style="color: #000000;">As with any medical treatment there is no guarantee of results, but our outcomes have been great for the vast majority of patients.</span></li></ul><p><span style="color: #000000;">Our lab has over 8 years specializing in Mesenchymal Stem Cell research. <span style="color: #00ccff;"><a style="color: #00ccff;" href="https://dreambody.clinic/index.php/certified-stem-cells/" rel="nofollow">See Stem Cell Certification by Clicking Here.</a></span></span></p><p><span style="color: #000000;">As with any medical treatment, there is no guarantee of success.</span></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
