        <div class="dbc-container dbc-column-gap-default">
          <div class="dbc-column dbc-col-100 dbc-top-column dbc-element dbc-element-238c2ef" data-id="238c2ef" data-element_type="column">
            <div class="dbc-widget-wrap dbc-element-populated">
              <div class="dbc-element dbc-element-d70e2b5 dbc-widget dbc-widget-text-editor" data-id="d70e2b5" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
                <div class="dbc-widget-container">
                  <p><span style="color: #000000;">The mesenchymal stem cell P-shot, also known as the Priapus Shot, is a medical treatment that involves the use of stem cells to enhance sexual performance, Enhance Sensation and treat erectile dysfunction. It is a non-invasive procedure where we take 50 million mesenchymal stem cells (MSCs) mixed with Platelet Rich Plasma (PRP) and inject 25 million MSCs into each side of the penis shaft. These stem cells have the potential to regenerate and repair damaged tissues, stimulate blood flow, improve sensitivity, and enhance the overall performance of the penis. The P-shot has gained popularity due to its purported ability to improve erectile function and promote sexual satisfaction. </span></p><p><span style="color: #000000;">There are several ways in which the stem cell p shot works. These include:</span></p><ol><li><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Tissue regeneration:</strong> Stem cells have the ability to guide differentiation and regeneration of various cell types and can potentially regenerate damaged tissues in the penis. This can lead to improved erectile function and tissue health.</span></p></li><li><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Neovascularization:</strong> Injected stem cells may promote the formation of new blood vessels in the penis, which can enhance blood circulation and oxygen supply to the erectile tissue. Improved blood flow is crucial for achieving and maintaining an erection.</span></p></li><li><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Anti-inflammatory effects:</strong> Stem cells may have anti-inflammatory properties that can help reduce inflammation and promote healing in the penile tissues. Inflammation can contribute to erectile dysfunction and other sexual problems.</span></p></li><li><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Growth factor production:</strong> Stem cells can secrete growth factors, which are proteins that regulate cell growth, tissue repair, and healing. These growth factors may stimulate the growth and repair of penile tissues, potentially leading to increased sensitivity and sexual performance.</span></p></li><li><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Nerve regeneration and sensitization:</strong> Stem cells may enhance nerve regeneration and promote nerve sensitization in the penis, improving sensations and sexual pleasure.</span></p></li></ol><p><span style="color: #000000;">You have no idea how much sensation you have lost in your penis until you get it back. After treatment many patients have told us that it is like being 18 again. This improved sensation usually lasts, but after about 3 to 6 months it becomes the new normal and you get accustomed to it. As with any medical treatment there is no guarantee of results, but our outcomes have been great for the vast majority of patients.</span></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
