      <section class="dbc-section dbc-top-section dbc-element dbc-element-aa6d2a5 dbc-section-boxed dbc-section-height-default dbc-section-height-default" data-id="aa6d2a5" data-element_type="section">
        <div class="dbc-container dbc-column-gap-default">
          <div class="dbc-column dbc-col-100 dbc-top-column dbc-element dbc-element-280a780" data-id="280a780" data-element_type="column">
            <div class="dbc-widget-wrap dbc-element-populated">
              <div class="dbc-element dbc-element-020fdc9 dbc-widget dbc-widget-text-editor" data-id="020fdc9" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
                <div class="dbc-widget-container">
                  <p><span style="color: #000000;">The use of mesenchymal stem cells (MSCs) in healing an enlarged prostate, also known as benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) is a highly effected way to get your prostate back in good health and to normal size again. MSCs have are used for their therapeutic effects in various medical conditions, including BPH.</span></p><p><span style="color: #000000;">Here are a few ways MSCs can help in the healing process of an enlarged prostate:</span></p><ol><li><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Anti-inflammatory properties:</strong> MSCs have shown anti-inflammatory effects, which can be beneficial in reducing inflammation and related symptoms associated with BPH. Chronic inflammation is considered one of the contributing factors in the development of BPH.</span></p></li><li><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Immunomodulatory effects:</strong> MSCs possess immunomodulatory properties, meaning they can regulate and modify the immune response. This may help in minimizing immune-mediated tissue damage and promoting tissue repair in the prostate.</span></p></li><li><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Paracrine signaling:</strong> MSCs are known to secrete various growth factors, cytokines, and chemokines, which can stimulate tissue regeneration and repair. These secreted molecules can potentially induce beneficial effects on the prostate tissue, promoting its healing.</span></p></li></ol>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
